{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/hover-effect-on-a-box-with-content/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"ecc3bfbd-8fb6-53b8-a492-5f64221cc21d","parent":{"relativePath":"blog/2021-02-04-hover-effect-on-a-box-with-content.md"},"fields":{"slug":"/hover-effect-on-a-box-with-content/"},"html":"<p>What I'd like to create as the frontend of my Self-Service Tool is two boxes to choose what type of request user wants to create. For now I have created the boxes. Each of them has label and icon:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/01e16557670a92839224902d134a4595/29114/20210122-163018-xydswegkvf.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.73673036093418%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Desired interface with two clickable boxes\"\n        title=\"Desired interface with two clickable boxes\"\n        src=\"/static/01e16557670a92839224902d134a4595/29114/20210122-163018-xydswegkvf.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/01e16557670a92839224902d134a4595/1f09d/20210122-163018-xydswegkvf.png 471w,\n/static/01e16557670a92839224902d134a4595/f1901/20210122-163018-xydswegkvf.png 942w,\n/static/01e16557670a92839224902d134a4595/29114/20210122-163018-xydswegkvf.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>I'd like to add an üåü hover indicator üåü so that users notice that it's clickable üñ±.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>NOTE</strong>: Buttons in PowerApps currently doesn't support changing to hand cursor (neither automatically nor manually). You can üó≥ vote for that feature üó≥ to be added <a href=\"https://powerusers.microsoft.com/t5/Power-Apps-Ideas/Buttons-in-powerapps-form-should-have-an-option-to-change-to/idi-p/278246\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">on Power Apps Community forum</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Fortunately, we have <code class=\"language-text\">HoverFill</code> property, where we could set the faded color of the <code class=\"language-text\">Fill</code>. We'll be using <a href=\"https://powerapps.microsoft.com/en-us/blog/formulas-launch-to-self-and-self-operator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><code class=\"language-text\">Self</code> operator introduced last year</a>.</p>\n<p>The formula to use is</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"powershell\"><pre class=\"language-powershell\"><code class=\"language-powershell\">ColorFade<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>Self<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Fill<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span>0<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"setting-hoverfill-value-for-rectangle\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#setting-hoverfill-value-for-rectangle\" aria-label=\"setting hoverfill value for rectangle permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Setting HoverFill value for rectangle</h2>\n<p>We can apply the formula to all the elements we have by clicking them on <strong>Tree view</strong> with <strong>CTRL</strong> pressed. Then, from the property dropdown, we can choose <code class=\"language-text\">HoverFill</code> and then paste the formula in the function field:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1920px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7d77be71145b4de31a181dc9e7685908/29114/20210125-170743-a5dxxntv28.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 43.73673036093418%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Applying formula to multiple elements\"\n        title=\"Applying formula to multiple elements\"\n        src=\"/static/7d77be71145b4de31a181dc9e7685908/29114/20210125-170743-a5dxxntv28.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7d77be71145b4de31a181dc9e7685908/1f09d/20210125-170743-a5dxxntv28.png 471w,\n/static/7d77be71145b4de31a181dc9e7685908/f1901/20210125-170743-a5dxxntv28.png 942w,\n/static/7d77be71145b4de31a181dc9e7685908/29114/20210125-170743-a5dxxntv28.png 1920w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>At first glance it seems to be working fine. However, if we go into details, it's not completely correct:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1523px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/e2c7416b402fbe01bd3d66df4ac517a2/6fcb6/20210204-205027-000012.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.422505307855626%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Incorrect hover behavior\"\n        title=\"Incorrect hover behavior\"\n        src=\"/static/e2c7416b402fbe01bd3d66df4ac517a2/6fcb6/20210204-205027-000012.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/e2c7416b402fbe01bd3d66df4ac517a2/1f09d/20210204-205027-000012.png 471w,\n/static/e2c7416b402fbe01bd3d66df4ac517a2/f1901/20210204-205027-000012.png 942w,\n/static/e2c7416b402fbe01bd3d66df4ac517a2/6fcb6/20210204-205027-000012.png 1523w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1523px) 100vw, 1523px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The reason of that behavior is that we have some elements on top of the rectangle. When we hover the cursor over the rectangle itself, it's fine. If we move cursor to the elements, rectangle is no longer hovered.</p>\n<p>We'd also need to copy the value of <code class=\"language-text\">OnSelect</code> to all the elements, which makes it more complex. üëé Imagine troubleshooting non-working formula only to discover that you forgot to update the function on one of the elements.</p>\n<h2 id=\"creating-rectangle-on-top\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#creating-rectangle-on-top\" aria-label=\"creating rectangle on top permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Creating rectangle on top</h2>\n<p>The most straightforward solution is to create transparent ‚¨ú rectangle on top of the existing ones.</p>\n<p>We'll name it similarly to the existing ones, so we can easily find the pair of them. For example, I name the bottom one <code class=\"language-text\">RectPhoneBg</code> and the top one <code class=\"language-text\">RectPhoneFg</code>.</p>\n<p>Now let's edit some properties as below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>X</strong> = RectPhoneBg.X</li>\n<li><strong>Y</strong> = RectPhoneBg.Y</li>\n<li><strong>Width</strong> = RectPhoneBg.Width</li>\n<li><strong>Height</strong> = RectPhoneBg.Height</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We set the position so that the top layer is always in the same place as the bottom one. üëçBuuut, now our top layer covers the whole content. </p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 1366px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/33efe2d9ba9ed497fef6b359456c1eda/ad00e/20210204-220455-000017.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 45.222929936305725%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Top rectangle covering the content\"\n        title=\"Top rectangle covering the content\"\n        src=\"/static/33efe2d9ba9ed497fef6b359456c1eda/ad00e/20210204-220455-000017.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/33efe2d9ba9ed497fef6b359456c1eda/1f09d/20210204-220455-000017.png 471w,\n/static/33efe2d9ba9ed497fef6b359456c1eda/f1901/20210204-220455-000017.png 942w,\n/static/33efe2d9ba9ed497fef6b359456c1eda/ad00e/20210204-220455-000017.png 1366w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 1366px) 100vw, 1366px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Let's make it transparent by setting <code class=\"language-text\">Fill</code> to</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"powershell\"><pre class=\"language-powershell\"><code class=\"language-powershell\">RGBA<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>255<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 255<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 255<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>The values of RGB don't matter as we set alpha to 0, which makes the element fully transparent. Now we want to create hover effect. </p>\n<p>We can use transparency so that the blue color from the background becomes a bit darker. For example create black element with alpha values of 0.2:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"powershell\"><pre class=\"language-powershell\"><code class=\"language-powershell\">RGBA<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>0<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>2<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Now we have created hover effect for the whole element üí™</p>\n<p>The only remaining task to do is to move <code class=\"language-text\">OnSelect</code> value to our top element. In current state, nothing happens when we click as we never reach the bottom element. Once we correct that, we have fully working interface!</p>\n<p><img src=\"/static/56e303a38264a84b313342d3d5154108/hover-working-fine.gif\" alt=\"Hoever working fine\"></p>","frontmatter":{"date":"2021-02-04 19:18","title":"Hover effect on a box with content in Power Apps","description":"Learn how to create hover effect on a box containing some content inside in Power Apps, so you can create modern interface for your application.","tags":["power apps","power platform"]}}},"pageContext":{"id":"ecc3bfbd-8fb6-53b8-a492-5f64221cc21d"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2483265550"]}